                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "700"
                                                },
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "LRueB",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 49.59375,
                                                  "name": " When he moved from The Jam into The Style Council",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 343,
                                                  "content": " When he moved from The Jam into The Style Council, Weller deliberately widened the palette toward jazz, synthpop, house, R&B, and sophisticated pop. In his own retrospective comments, this was also the period when he became disillusioned with guitar and played it less and less, so the instrument often serves the arrangement rather than dominating it. (guitarworld.com)",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                                }
                                              ]
                                            }
                                          ]
                                        },
                                        {
                                          "type": "frame",
                                          "id": "lkKcP",
                                          "name": "List Item",
                                          "width": "fill_container",
                                          "height": 297.5625,
                                          "stroke": {
                                            "align": "inside",
                                            "thickness": 1
                                          },
                                          "layout": "none",
                                          "children": [
                                            {
                                              "type": "frame",
                                              "id": "qT7Ry",
                                              "x": 0,
                                              "y": 0,
                                              "name": "Paragraph",
                                              "width": 353.6015625,
                                              "height": 297.5625,
                                              "stroke": {
                                                "align": "inside",
                                                "thickness": 1
                                              },
                                              "layout": "none",
                                              "children": [
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "c9f8T",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 0,
                                                  "name": "Early solo / ‘90s renaissance (1992 through Wild W",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 336,
                                                  "content": "Early solo / ‘90s renaissance (1992 through Wild Wood and Stanley Road): rediscovered guitar voice",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "700"
                                                },
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "bWCBQ",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 74.390625,
                                                  "name": " The key shift here is not just “solo career” but ",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 349,
                                                  "content": " The key shift here is not just “solo career” but reconnection. Weller said that in the 1990s he “rediscovered” guitar after the Style Council years, and you can hear that in the more organic, rootsy blend of acoustic strumming and fuller electric playing. This is the era where his guitar style becomes less angular than The Jam, but more central again—earthier, warmer, and more song-serving. (musicradar.com)",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                                }
                                              ]
                                            }
                                          ]
                                        },
                                        {
                                          "type": "frame",
                                          "id": "ViJA4",
                                          "name": "List Item",
                                          "width": "fill_container",
                                          "height": 272.765625,
                                          "stroke": {
                                            "align": "inside",
                                            "thickness": 1
                                          },
                                          "layout": "none",
                                          "children": [
                                            {
                                              "type": "frame",
                                              "id": "hU1Y3",
                                              "x": 0,
                                              "y": 0,
                                              "name": "Paragraph",
                                              "width": 353.6015625,
                                              "height": 272.765625,
                                              "stroke": {
                                                "align": "inside",
                                                "thickness": 1
                                              },
                                              "layout": "none",
                                              "children": [
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "Elndb",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 0,
                                                  "name": "Acoustic/songwriter emphasis (around Days of Speed",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 339,
                                                  "content": "Acoustic/songwriter emphasis (around Days of Speed, early 2000s): songs stripped to guitar and voice",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "700"
                                                },
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "PycH7",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 74.390625,
                                                  "name": " The acoustic period is really a sub-era of the so",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 349,
                                                  "content": " The acoustic period is really a sub-era of the solo years, but it matters because it exposes the core of his writing. The Days of Speed framing—just Weller and guitar—highlights his Gibson-led acoustic side and shows that his guitar identity isn’t only about electric mod riffs; it also rests on durable chord writing and live delivery. (musicradar.com)",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                                }
                                              ]
                                            }
                                          ]
                                        },
                                        {
                                          "type": "frame",
                                          "id": "WqELI",
                                          "name": "List Item",
                                          "width": "fill_container",
                                          "height": 322.359375,
                                          "stroke": {
                                            "align": "inside",
                                            "thickness": 1
                                          },
                                          "layout": "none",
                                          "children": [
                                            {
                                              "type": "frame",
                                              "id": "27rKv",
                                              "x": 0,
                                              "y": 0,
                                              "name": "Paragraph",
                                              "width": 353.6015625,
                                              "height": 322.359375,
                                              "stroke": {
                                                "align": "inside",
                                                "thickness": 1
                                              },
                                              "layout": "none",
                                              "children": [
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "NGcsU",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 0,
                                                  "name": "Later solo work, especially from 22 Dreams onward ",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 348,
                                                  "content": "Later solo work, especially from 22 Dreams onward (2008+): eclectic, exploratory, texture-first guitar",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "700"
                                                },
                                                {
                                                  "type": "text",
                                                  "id": "peRXW",
                                                  "x": 0,
                                                  "y": 74.390625,
                                                  "name": " By this stage, Weller’s records become more overt",
                                                  "fill": "#111111ff",
                                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                                  "width": 353,
                                                  "content": " By this stage, Weller’s records become more overtly genre-crossing and experimental. He described this period as “wide open,” and interviews from Sonik Kicks/Saturns Pattern show him favoring a broader range of guitars and sounds—Danelectro, Telecaster, SG, effects, and unusual textures—rather than relying on one signature voice. In other words: early Weller had a trademark guitar sound; later Weller has a trademark curiosity. (guitarworld.com)",
                                                  "lineHeight": 1.5499999523162842,
                                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                                  "fontSize": 16,
                                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                                }
                                              ]
                                            }
                                          ]
                                        }
                                      ]
                                    },
